p:
In recent years, MaxEnt software (MaxEnt version 3.3.3k, 
 http://www.cs.princeton.edu/s˜chapire/maxent/) has frequently been used to simulate shifts in species ranges under current and future climate scenarios (
 Ponce-Reyes et al., 2012; 
 Wong et al., 2013; 
 Cooper et al., 2016). This software is popular because it requires only presence-only data. Comparative studies have consistently shown that MaxEnt has excellent performance and outperforms than many other methods (such as GARP) in estimating potential species distributions, particularly when sample sizes are small (
 Elith et al., 2006; 
 Bosso et al., 2016; 
 Sultana et al., 2017). Moreover, some studies found that this software performed well regardless of the number or geographical extent of species records, compared to the performance of mahalannobis typicalities, random forests methods and other methods (
 Bosso et al., 2016; 
 Hernandez et al., 2006; 
 Elith et al., 2011).
